AB  - Using GBD 2021 data (ages 5–24), anxiety disorders became the leading cause of nonfatal disability in 2021, accounting for 12.9 million YLDs — up from third place pre-pandemic. The pandemic added an estimated 165.9 extra new cases per 100,000 globally in 2021 beyond pre-pandemic trends. Burden was highest among females aged 15–24 and in high-SDI regions. **Design:** GBD epidemiological analysis. **Limitations:** relies on modelled GBD estimates; clinical diagnosis rates may undercount real burden.
