AB  - GBD 2021 analysis across 204 countries: global incidence of anxiety disorders among 10–24-year-olds increased 52% between 1990 and 2021, with a sharp acceleration post-2019. Highest incidence in middle-SDI regions; largest increases in high-SDI countries. Bullying victimisation was the most significant identified risk factor. **Design:** GBD trend analysis. **Limitations:** ecological design; cannot infer causality.
