AB  - JAMA Pediatrics meta-analysis of 29 studies (N = 80,879): during the first year of COVID-19, about 1 in 4 youth globally had clinically elevated depression symptoms and 1 in 5 had clinically elevated anxiety symptoms — roughly double pre-pandemic estimates. Rates were higher later in the pandemic and higher in girls. **Design:** meta-analysis of cross-sectional studies. **Limitations:** mostly cross-sectional; clinically elevated symptoms ≠ diagnosed disorder.
