AB  - UK CPRD cohort (N = 9.1 million, 2003–2018): incidence rate of diagnosed anxiety disorders in CYP more than tripled (IRR 3.51, 95% CI 3.18–3.89). Absolute rates were highest for depression and anxiety disorders; largest relative increases were for neurodevelopmental disorders in girls. **Design:** population-based UK primary care cohort. **Limitations:** changes may partly reflect improved recognition rather than true incidence.
