AB  - British Journal of Psychiatry reanalysis of England MHCYP surveys 2004 and 2017 (N = 13,561): prevalence of emotional disorders rose from 3.9% to 6.0% (RR 1.63), driven largely by anxiety disorders (3.5% → 5.4%). Largest increases were in panic, separation anxiety, social phobia, and PTSD. Change was significant only in White CYP, not Black/minority ethnic CYP. **Design:** repeated cross-sectional national survey. **Limitations:** two time-points only; no post-2017 data.
