DO  - 10.1007/s10567-018-0266-5
JO  - Clinical Child and Family Psychology Review
AB  - Meta-analysis of 14 RCTs (N = 5,970 children aged ≤13): universal school-based programs produced small effects on depressive symptoms post-program (g = 0.172) and at long-term follow-up (g = 0.180), but no significant effect on anxiety at any time point. FRIENDS programme and longer programs showed some beneficial effects on both. **Design:** meta-analysis. **Limitations:** very small effect sizes; no anxiety prevention effect overall.
